  "title": "CRANE OPERATOR",
  "description": "<p>•\tOperate crawler cranes safely and efficiently on construction sites to lift, move, and position heavy materials and equipment.</p><p>•\tRead and interpret construction drawings, site plans, and lifting instructions.</p><p>•\tInspect crane equipment daily before operation and perform routine maintenance checks.</p><p>•\tEnsure loads are properly secured and lifted according to safety regulations and load charts.</p><p>•\tCommunicate effectively with riggers, signalers, and site supervisors to coordinate lifts.</p><p>•\tMonitor crane performance and report any malfunctions, defects, or safety hazards.</p><p>•\tFollow all safety procedures, regulations, and site protocols at all times.</p><p>•\tAssist in planning lifts, including calculating load weight, lift radius, and required crane configuration.</p><p></p><p>Key Skills & Requirements:</p><p>•\tValid certification/license to operate crawler cranes.</p><p>•\tProven experience operating heavy lifting equipment on construction sites.</p><p>•\tStrong understanding of construction site safety and rigging procedures.</p><p>•\tAbility to work outdoors in various weather conditions.</p><p>•\tGood communication skills to coordinate with team members.</p>",
